1.b: Good transportation, schools, churches, etc. Fair section of old houses near Harvard Square

areaDesc.5: Apartments on Prescott are fairly high class. Harvard St. is better than the balance of  the area. Houses have value for rooming house purposes, being near Harvard University. Majority of 2 family units are converted singles. A few negro families have moved in on Dame St. and threaten to spread.

1.b: desirable residential area of high grade houses with better class occupant. Well located with good transportation. Adjacent to Harvard University.

areaDesc.5: Harvard University owns a street of small apartments called Holden Green which are available only to married Harvard students. The bulk of the houses are built on large sized lots. Area is considered one of the best residential sections of Cambridge with few units available for sale at any time.

1.b: good transportation, schools, etc. Overlooks the Charles River and parkway. Very convenient location.

areaDesc.5: This small area has a general mixture of all size houses in all degrees of condition. There are several garages and filling stations in the neighborhood. Properties range in value from $1,000 to $10,000.

1.c: Obsolscence. Low class occupants. Poor housing. Congested area.
1.b: near diversified employment. Good tranportation, schools, etc.
same as area D-1 except practically solid Italian with 10% negro.
Desirable section of modest houses. Good transportation, schools, churches, etc.

areaDesc.5: Massachusetts Avenue frontages are practically all small business places and as such have considerable value

1.b: good location. Adjacent to Harvard University.

areaDesc.5: The greatest value of housing in this neighborhood is for rooming house purposes. Recent construction of dormitories by Harvard University has eliminated some of the demand from this source.

1.b: good location of desirable older homes in high class section

areaDesc.5: There are several high grade apartments in this neighborhood. The bulk of the 2 family units are converted singles.

1.b: Desirable neighborhood of good character. Well located with good transportation, schools, etc.

areaDesc.5: Smaller houses did not ______ much in value because of proximity to high class neighborhood. These units are concentrated near Mt. Auburn which itself is very mediocre as Brewer, Hunting Place. Along Charles River Road are located some high class apartments renting for $75 to $225.

1.b: desirable neighborhood of high class people

areaDesc.5: Longfellow mansion is in this neighborhood which gives the area desirable character. Houses are old but very well helf with few being offered for sale at any time. Many large estates are scattered through the area which in time will be subdivided.

1.b: very desirable two family section of good character. Well located with good transportation, schools, etc.

areaDesc.5: Properties are very well held with few offered for sale at any time. Although somewhat old the section continues as one of the desirable neighborhoods of Cambridge.

1.b: Newest development in Cambridge. Good construction of modern houses with high class occupant. Restricted as to price and style.

areaDesc.5: Well planned development of good houses in a very desirable location. Because of limited room for new building is Cambridge, this area will hold up very well. Protected by fence and elevation from 3rd class section.

1.b: desirable high grade residential section, well maintained. High class occupant. Property well held.

areaDesc.5: One of two comparatively new sections in Cambridge. Few of these are offered for sale and no encroachment is imminent. Immediately adjacent are several high grade private schools.
Two family units are converted singles. Poorest third grade section of Cambridge with little upswing in prices anticipated.

1.a: This is a good apartment house area with rentals from $50 up. Overlooking the Charles River the neighborhood is one of the most desirable of its kind in the entire area.

1.c: obsolescence - negro concentration - foreign concentration - scattered business

areaDesc.5: People have no reserves and rents are not always paid in poor times. Foreign concentrated at western end and negro in central part. Negro is good class occupant.
